.TH "CIRCLECI-MIGRATE" "1" "Jun 2026" "circleci-migrate" "CircleCI Org Migration CLI"

.SH NAME
circleci-migrate-secrets-extract - Capture a context's or project's secret values from the job environment.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcircleci-migrate secrets extract --manifest  (--context  | --project ) [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
extract reads the variable names for one context or project from the
manifest, looks each value up in the current environment, and records the
found values in a secret bundle (merging into an existing bundle if present).

.PP
Run this inside a CircleCI job that injects the target's variables:
  - For a context, the job must reference exactly that context.
  - For project variables, the job must run within that project.

.PP
When --encrypt is set, the bundle is written as an age-encrypted file
(\&.age) and the plaintext file is NOT written. Provide the recipient's
public key via --recipient (inline string) or --recipient-file (path to a .pub
or age recipients file).

.PP
Examples:
  circleci-migrate secrets extract --manifest manifest.json --context deploy-prod
  circleci-migrate secrets extract --manifest manifest.json --project gh/acme/web -o secrets.json
  circleci-migrate secrets extract --manifest manifest.json --context deploy-prod \\
    --encrypt --recipient-file /tmp/migration.pub


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--context\fP=""
	Context name to capture (mutually exclusive with --project)

.PP
\fB--encrypt\fP[=false]
	Encrypt the output bundle with age (writes \&.age; requires --recipient or --recipient-file)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for extract

.PP
\fB--manifest\fP=""
	Path to the export manifest (required)

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="secrets.json"
	Path to the secret bundle to write/append

.PP
\fB--project\fP=""
	Project slug to capture (mutually exclusive with --context)

.PP
\fB--recipient\fP=""
	age or SSH public key recipient string (ssh-ed25519/ssh-rsa/age1...)

.PP
\fB--recipient-file\fP=""
	Path to an SSH public key (.pub) or age recipients file

.PP
\fB--strict\fP[=false]
	Fail if any expected variable is missing from the environment


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug logging

.PP
\fB--dest-token\fP=""
	API token for the destination org (env: CIRCLECI_DEST_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--host\fP="https://circleci.com"
	CircleCI host URL (env: CIRCLECI_HOST)

.PP
\fB--source-token\fP=""
	API token for the source org (env: CIRCLECI_SOURCE_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	Personal API token — fallback for both orgs (env: CIRCLECI_CLI_TOKEN)


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcircleci-migrate-secrets(1)\fP


